This paper is about improving the performance of stochastic optimization algorithms in deep learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the generalization performance of large-batch stochastic gradient descent, which is a common optimization algorithm used in deep learning. Other likely categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these sub-categories are also relevant to deep learning and optimization.
